<div id="ftn26">
<p><a href="file://lifile01/userdata/aoliver/Redirection/Desktop/LOWY/BOBO%20LO,%20CHINA%20RUSSIA%20GLOBAL%20ORDER/Bobo%20Lo,%20Global%20Order%20in%20the%20Shadow%20of%20the%20Coronavirus%20-%20China,%20Russia%20and%20the%20West,%20FINAL%20270720.doc#_ftnref26" name="_ftn26" title="" id="_ftn26">[26]</a> As Richard McGregor observes, “[i]n the post-Mao era … the United States has by and large been, at least until Donald Trump’s election, the indispensable enabler of China’s rise” — <em>Xi Jinping: The Backlash</em>, Lowy Institute Paper (Penguin Random House Australia, 2019), 16.</p>
