<div id="ftn38">
<p><a href="file://lifile01/userdata/aoliver/Redirection/Desktop/LOWY/BOBO%20LO,%20CHINA%20RUSSIA%20GLOBAL%20ORDER/Bobo%20Lo,%20Global%20Order%20in%20the%20Shadow%20of%20the%20Coronavirus%20-%20China,%20Russia%20and%20the%20West,%20FINAL%20270720.doc#_ftnref38" name="_ftn38" title="" id="_ftn38">[38]</a> As Andrey Kortunov notes, in many respects Beijing and Moscow enjoy a smoother and more productive interaction than many allied relationships — “Who Will Build the New World Order?”, Russian International Affairs Council, 6 June 2019, <a href="https://russiancouncil.ru/en/analytics-and-comments/analytics/who-will-build-the-new-world-order/">https://russiancouncil.ru/en/analytics-and-comments/analytics/who-will-build-the-new-world-order/</a>.</p>
