<div id="ftn39">
<p><a href="file://lifile01/userdata/aoliver/Redirection/Desktop/LOWY/BOBO%20LO,%20CHINA%20RUSSIA%20GLOBAL%20ORDER/Bobo%20Lo,%20Global%20Order%20in%20the%20Shadow%20of%20the%20Coronavirus%20-%20China,%20Russia%20and%20the%20West,%20FINAL%20270720.doc#_ftnref39" name="_ftn39" title="" id="_ftn39">[39]</a> Many American commentators tend to view China–Russia relations almost exclusively through the prism of American interests. Thus, Michael Kofman claims that “their alignment is principally a balancing one against US efforts to retain primacy in international politics” — in Michael Kofman, “Towards a Sino–Russian Entente?”, <em>Riddle</em>, 29 November 2019, <a href="https://www.ridl.io/en/towards-a-sino-russian-entente/">https://www.ridl.io/en/towards-a-sino-russian-entente/</a>.</p>
