<div id="ftn43">
<p><a href="file://lifile01/userdata/aoliver/Redirection/Desktop/LOWY/BOBO%20LO,%20CHINA%20RUSSIA%20GLOBAL%20ORDER/Bobo%20Lo,%20Global%20Order%20in%20the%20Shadow%20of%20the%20Coronavirus%20-%20China,%20Russia%20and%20the%20West,%20FINAL%20270720.doc#_ftnref43" name="_ftn43" title="" id="_ftn43">[43]</a> See Yaroslav Trofimov and Thomas Grove, “Weary Russia Tries to Avoid Entanglement in U.S.–China Spat”, <em>Wall Street Journal</em>, 22 June 2020, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/weary-russia-tries-to-avoid-entanglement-in-u-s-china-spat-11592654401">https://www.wsj.com/articles/weary-russia-tries-to-avoid-entanglement-in-u-s-china-spat-11592654401</a>; also Dmitri Trenin, “How Russia Can Maintain Equilibrium in the Post-Pandemic Bipolar World”, Carnegie Moscow Center, 1 May 2020, <a href="https://carnegie.ru/commentary/81702">https://carnegie.ru/commentary/81702</a>.</p>
